[2026-07-20T12:09:49.029Z] [INFO]         "content": "      # See packages/app-builder-lib/src/targets/mac/MacTargetHelper.ts: only the\n      # `qualifier === \"-\"` branch yields an Identity when no certificate exists.\n      # Without `-c.mac.identity=-` the produced .app had no _CodeSignature, so the\n      # pre-upload smoke test failed with \"missing its signed CodeResources\n      # envelope\" and macOS assets were never published. Passing identity=\"-\" makes\n      # electron-builder reach doSign(), which runs our ad-hoc hook (deep ad-hoc\n      # sign via @electron/osx-sign + an explicit root-bundle re-seal).\n      - name: Package desktop app (macOS ad-hoc)\n        if: matrix.ebflag == '--mac' && steps.mac_secrets.outputs.has_secrets != 'true'\n        working-directory: desktop\n        env:\n          CSC_IDENTITY_AUTO_DISCOVERY: \"false\"\n          MACOS_ADHOC_SIGN: \"1\"\n          # Issue #808: electron-builder's isSignAllowed() bails out with\n          # \"Current build is a part of pull request, code signing will be\n          # skipped\" whenever GITHUB_BASE_REF is set (builder-util\n          # `isPullRequest()`), so the pull-request dry run produced an unsigned\n          # .app with no CodeResources and the smoke test failed. The security\n          # warning attached to this flag is about *secret* certificates leaking\n          # to fork builds; this step only runs when no signing secrets exist and\n          # signs ad-hoc with identity `-`, so there is nothing to leak.\n          CSC_FOR_PULL_REQUEST: \"true\"\n          FORMAL_AI_MACOS_SIGN_DEBUG: \"1\"\n          DEBUG: electron-builder,electron-osx-sign*\n        run: npx --no-install electron-builder ${{ matrix.ebflag }} --publish never -c.mac.notarize=false -c.mac.identity=- -c.mac.sign=./scripts/adhoc-sign-mac.cjs\n\n      - name: Normalize desktop artifact names\n        working-directory: desktop\n        run: node scripts/normalize-artifacts.mjs\n\n      - name: Smoke test macOS release artifacts",
[2026-07-20T12:09:49.029Z] [INFO]         "is_error": false
[2026-07-20T12:09:49.029Z] [INFO]       }
[2026-07-20T12:09:49.029Z] [INFO]     ]
