[2026-07-20T12:23:16.553Z] [INFO]         "text": "Work is committed and pushed; CI is running in the background. Summary of what I found and did:\n\n**Two independent defects, both traced to root cause from the run logs** (all 10 MB of logs + job metadata archived under `dev/log/issues/810/pulls/811/`, analysis in `analysis.md`).\n\n**Defect A — `Auto Release` was permanently deadlocked (fixed).**\n`scripts/self-hosting-metric.rs` requires a `Formal-AI-Evidence` document to contain its own session id. Commit `10e65ae2`'s does not — I verified directly:\n`git show 10e65ae2:…/analysis.md | grep -c issue-804-claude-20260720` → `0`.\n\nThe timeline is what made it fatal: the `evidence-check` gate landed in `39fdef91`, *after* `10e65ae2` merged (`git merge-base --is-ancestor` confirms). `record_release` measures `<last tag>..HEAD`, so that commit sits in the range until a new tag is cut — and cutting a tag requires the release to succeed. No future commit could break the loop.\n\nFix: an explicit `EvidencePolicy`. The PR gate stays `Strict`; `record_release` is `Lenient` — it warns and leaves the commit unattributed, so the metric can only under-report, never over-report. Regression test reproduces the exact shape of `10e65ae2`; `5 passed; 0 failed`. My own commit passes the strict gate (`100.00% (44386/44386)`).\n\n**Defect B — macOS Chrome framework seal (instrumented, not fixed).**\n`codesign` failed with \"unsealed contents present in the root directory of an embedded framework\". The logs prove the sign hook *was* invoked (electron-builder's `• executing custom sign`, plus `--timestamp=none` from our `optionsForFile`) — but contain **zero** `[adhoc-sign-mac]` lines despite `FORMAL_AI_MACOS_SIGN_DEBUG=1`. So whether the ignore predicate was consulted-and-declined or never called is still unknown, and those need different fixes. Rather than guess (as the two prior attempts did), I made the diagnostics unloseable: synchronous `fs.writeSync(2, …)` instead of async pipe writes, plus `considered=N skipped=M` counters emitted from a `finally` block so they survive an aborting build. Per-file trace stays behind the env var, off by default.\n\n**Two things I deliberately did not do**, both recorded as open gaps rather than dropped: no upstream issue filed (would be a guess until the counters land), and the file-by-file comparison against the three `link-foundation/*` pipeline templates — requirement 7 in the issue — is **not done**. Neither failure originated in template-derived workflow structure, so it's separate work, but the issue does ask for it and it remains outstanding.\n\nPR: https://github.com/link-assistant/formal-ai/pull/811 (marked ready for review)"
